 letters, educational treatises, histories, catechisms and children’s bibles), showing how concepts of childhood related to debates about Irish nationality, politics and history across these two centuries.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aAuthors, Irishy17th century. 0aAuthors, Irishy18th century. 0aChildren in literature. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / English, Irish, Scottish, Welsh.2bisacsh  a1641 Rebellion.  aChildhood Studies.  aIrish Anglican identity.  aIrish Studies.  aJohn Temple.  aJonathan Swift.  aPuritanism.  aStephen Cullen.  aWilliam Chaigneau.  aWilliam Molyneux.  aanglican wiriting.  acatechisms.  achild of wrath.  achildhood studies.  achildren’s bibles.  ainnocence.  athe child.  athe irish child.  avulnerability.1 aKilleen, Jarlath, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packagez978311120645540uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152616198740uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526161987423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526161987/original  a978-3-11-120645-5  Manchester University Press 2023 eBook-Packageb2023  aGBV-deGruyter-alles